2.1.1.2 Harmonisation algorithm

To compute h_asthma from the study-specific variable it has to be recoded as follows:

  • some hedibX == 2 into 1
  • -9 into 997
  • -8 into 998
  • otherwise into 0

Age of diagnosis cannot be harmonized.

R script:

# Categorical variable harmonization
ELSA_ds_w1 <- tibble(id = ELSA_w1$id)
ELSA_ds_w1$h_asthma <- rep(0, length(ELSA_w1$id))
ELSA_ds_w1$h_asthma[which((ELSA_w1$hedib01 == 2 | ELSA_w1$hedib02 == 2 | ELSA_w1$hedib03 == 
    2 | ELSA_w1$hedib04 == 2 | ELSA_w1$hedib05 == 2 | ELSA_w1$hedib06 == 2 | 
    ELSA_w1$hedib07 == 2 | ELSA_w1$hedib08 == 2 | ELSA_w1$hedib09 == 2 | ELSA_w1$hedib10 == 
    2))] <- 1
ELSA_ds_w1$h_asthma[which(ELSA_w1$hedib01 == -9)] <- 997
ELSA_ds_w1$h_asthma[which(ELSA_w1$hedib01 == -8)] <- 998

# Global table
ELSA_ds <- ELSA_ds_w1
ELSA_ds$h_asthma_age <- rep(999, length(ELSA_ds$id))

2.1.2.2 Harmonisation algorithm

To compute h_asthma from the study-specific variable it has to be recoded as follows:

  • h_asthma w1 == 1 or some hedibX == 2 into 1
  • h_asthma w1 != 1 and hedib01 == -9 into 997
  • h_asthma w1 != 1 and hedib01 == -8 into 998
  • otherwise into 0

To compute h_asthma_age from the study-specific variable it has to be recoded as follows:

  • if h_asthma == 1 in w2 and 0 in w1, h_asthma_age = (year of interview w2-year of interview w1)/2+(year of interview w1 - ybirth)
  • if h_asthma == 0, h_asthma_age = 996
  • otherwise, h_asthma_age = 999

R script:

ELSA_w2 <- left_join(ELSA_w2, ELSA_ds, by = "id")

# Categorical variable harmonization
ELSA_ds_w2 <- tibble(id = ELSA_w2$id)
ELSA_ds_w2$h_asthma <- rep(0, length(ELSA_w2$id))
ELSA_ds_w2$h_asthma[which(ELSA_w2$h_asthma == 1 | ((ELSA_w2$hedib01 == 2 | ELSA_w2$hedib02 == 
    2 | ELSA_w2$hedib03 == 2 | ELSA_w2$hedib04 == 2)))] <- 1
ELSA_ds_w2$h_asthma[which((ELSA_w2$h_asthma != 1 | is.na(ELSA_w2$h_asthma)) & 
    ELSA_w2$hedib01 == -9)] <- 997
ELSA_ds_w2$h_asthma[which((ELSA_w2$h_asthma != 1 | is.na(ELSA_w2$h_asthma)) & 
    ELSA_w2$hedib01 == -8)] <- 998

# Continuous variable harmonization
ELSA_ds_w2$h_asthma_age <- rep(999, length(ELSA_w2$id))
ELSA_ds_w2$h_asthma_age[which(ELSA_ds_w2$h_asthma == 0)] <- 996
ELSA_ds_w2$h_asthma_age[which(ELSA_ds_w2$h_asthma == 1 & ELSA_w2$h_asthma == 
    0)] <- floor((ELSA_w2$yintw_w2[which(ELSA_ds_w2$h_asthma == 1 & ELSA_w2$h_asthma == 
    0)] + ELSA_w2$yintw_w1[which(ELSA_ds_w2$h_asthma == 1 & ELSA_w2$h_asthma == 
    0)])/2 - ELSA_w2$ybirth[which(ELSA_ds_w2$h_asthma == 1 & ELSA_w2$h_asthma == 
    0)])

# Update of global table
assign_merge <- function(endtib, sttib, log_vec = c(T), col_end_index = NULL, 
    col_st_index = NULL) {
    newtib <- full_join(endtib, sttib, by = "id")
    row.names(newtib) <- newtib$id
    newtib[log_vec, col_end_index] <- newtib[log_vec, col_st_index]
    id_ind <- match("id", names(newtib))
    newtib <- newtib[, c(id_ind, col_end_index)]
    names(newtib)[2] <- "x"
    newtib$x <- car::recode(newtib$x, "NA=999")
    names(newtib)[2] <- names(endtib)[col_end_index]
    newtib
}
ELSA_ds_prov <- ELSA_ds[, c(1, 2)]
ELSA_ds_prov <- assign_merge(ELSA_ds_prov, ELSA_ds_w2, log_vec = ELSA_ds_w2$id, 
    col_end_index = 2, col_st_index = 3)
ELSA_ds_aux <- ELSA_ds[, c(1, 3)]
ELSA_ds_aux <- assign_merge(ELSA_ds_aux, ELSA_ds_w2, log_vec = ELSA_ds_w2$id[which(ELSA_ds_w2$h_asthma != 
    999)], col_end_index = 2, col_st_index = 4)
ELSA_ds <- ELSA_ds_prov
ELSA_ds$h_asthma_age <- ELSA_ds_aux$h_asthma_age
rm(ELSA_ds_prov)
rm(ELSA_ds_aux)

2.1.3.2 Harmonisation algorithm

To compute h_asthma from the study-specific variable it has to be recoded as follows:

  • h_asthma previous == 1 or dhedibas == 1 into 1
  • h_asthma previous == 0 and dhedibas == 0 into 0
  • dhedibas == -1 into 996
  • otherwise into 999

To compute h_asthma_age from the study-specific variable it has to be recoded as follows:

  • if h_asthma == 1 in w3 and 0 in w2, h_asthma_age = (year of interview w3-year of interview w2)/2+(year of interview w2 - ybirth)
  • if h_asthma == 0, h_asthma_age = 996
  • otherwise, h_asthma_age = 999

R script:

ELSA_w3 <- left_join(ELSA_w3, ELSA_ds, by = "id")

# Categorical variable harmonization
ELSA_ds_w3 <- tibble(id = ELSA_w3$id)
ELSA_ds_w3$h_asthma <- rep(999, length(ELSA_w3$id))
ELSA_ds_w3$h_asthma[which((ELSA_w3$h_asthma != 1 | is.na(ELSA_w3$h_asthma)) & 
    (ELSA_w3$dhedibas == 0))] <- 0
ELSA_ds_w3$h_asthma[which(ELSA_w3$h_asthma == 1 | (ELSA_w3$dhedibas == 1))] <- 1
ELSA_ds_w3$h_asthma[which((ELSA_w3$h_asthma != 1 | is.na(ELSA_w3$h_asthma)) & 
    (ELSA_w3$dhedibas == -1))] <- 996

ELSA_w3 <- left_join(ELSA_w3, ELSA_ds_w2, by = "id", suffix = c("", "_w2"))

# Continuous variable harmonization
ELSA_ds_w3$h_asthma_age <- rep(999, length(ELSA_w3$id))
ELSA_ds_w3$h_asthma_age[which(ELSA_ds_w3$h_asthma == 0)] <- 996
ELSA_ds_w3$h_asthma_age[which(ELSA_ds_w3$h_asthma == 1 & ELSA_w3$h_asthma_w2 == 
    0 & ELSA_w3$ybirth != 998)] <- floor((ELSA_w3$yintw_w2[which(ELSA_ds_w3$h_asthma == 
    1 & ELSA_w3$h_asthma_w2 == 0 & ELSA_w3$ybirth != 998)] + ELSA_w3$yintw_w3[which(ELSA_ds_w3$h_asthma == 
    1 & ELSA_w3$h_asthma_w2 == 0 & ELSA_w3$ybirth != 998)])/2 - ELSA_w3$ybirth[which(ELSA_ds_w3$h_asthma == 
    1 & ELSA_w3$h_asthma_w2 == 0 & ELSA_w3$ybirth != 998)])
ELSA_ds_w3$h_asthma_age[which(ELSA_ds_w3$h_asthma == 1 & !is.na(ELSA_w3$h_asthma_age) & 
    !ELSA_w3$h_asthma_age %in% miss_values_vector)] <- ELSA_w3$h_asthma_age[which(ELSA_ds_w3$h_asthma == 
    1 & !is.na(ELSA_w3$h_asthma_age) & !ELSA_w3$h_asthma_age %in% miss_values_vector)]

# Update of global table

2.1.4.2 Harmonisation algorithm

To compute h_asthma from the study-specific variable it has to be recoded as follows:

  • h_asthma previous == 1 or hedibas == 1 into 1
  • h_asthma previous == 0 and hedibas == 0 into 0
  • dhedibas == -1 into 996
  • dhedibas == -9 into 997
  • dhedibas == -8 into 998
  • otherwise into 999

To compute h_asthma_age from the study-specific variable it has to be recoded as follows:

  • if h_asthma == 1 in w4 and 0 in w3, h_asthma_age = (year of interview w4-year of interview w3)/2+(year of interview w3 - ybirth)
  • if h_asthma == 0, h_asthma_age = 996
  • otherwise, h_asthma_age = 999

R script:

ELSA_w4 <- left_join(ELSA_w4, ELSA_ds, by = "id")

# Categorical variable harmonization
ELSA_ds_w4 <- tibble(id = ELSA_w4$id)
ELSA_ds_w4$h_asthma <- rep(999, length(ELSA_w4$id))
ELSA_ds_w4$h_asthma[which((ELSA_w4$h_asthma != 1 | is.na(ELSA_w4$h_asthma)) & 
    (ELSA_w4$hedibas == 0))] <- 0
ELSA_ds_w4$h_asthma[which(ELSA_w4$h_asthma == 1 | (ELSA_w4$hedibas == 1))] <- 1
ELSA_ds_w4$h_asthma[which((ELSA_w4$h_asthma != 1 | is.na(ELSA_w4$h_asthma)) & 
    ELSA_w4$hedibas == -1)] <- 996
ELSA_ds_w4$h_asthma[which((ELSA_w4$h_asthma != 1 | is.na(ELSA_w4$h_asthma)) & 
    ELSA_w4$hedibas == -9)] <- 997
ELSA_ds_w4$h_asthma[which((ELSA_w4$h_asthma != 1 | is.na(ELSA_w4$h_asthma)) & 
    ELSA_w4$hedibas == -8)] <- 998

ELSA_w4 <- left_join(ELSA_w4, ELSA_ds_w3, by = "id", suffix = c("", "_w3"))

# Continuous variable harmonization
ELSA_ds_w4$h_asthma_age <- rep(999, length(ELSA_w4$id))
ELSA_ds_w4$h_asthma_age[which(ELSA_ds_w4$h_asthma == 0)] <- 996
ELSA_ds_w4$h_asthma_age[which(ELSA_ds_w4$h_asthma == 1 & ELSA_w4$h_asthma_w3 == 
    0)] <- floor((ELSA_w4$yintw_w3[which(ELSA_ds_w4$h_asthma == 1 & ELSA_w4$h_asthma_w3 == 
    0)] + ELSA_w4$yintw_w4[which(ELSA_ds_w4$h_asthma == 1 & ELSA_w4$h_asthma_w3 == 
    0)])/2 - ELSA_w4$ybirth[which(ELSA_ds_w4$h_asthma == 1 & ELSA_w4$h_asthma_w3 == 
    0)])
ELSA_ds_w4$h_asthma_age[which(ELSA_ds_w4$h_asthma == 1 & !is.na(ELSA_w4$h_asthma_age) & 
    !ELSA_w4$h_asthma_age %in% miss_values_vector)] <- ELSA_w4$h_asthma_age[which(ELSA_ds_w4$h_asthma == 
    1 & !is.na(ELSA_w4$h_asthma_age) & !ELSA_w4$h_asthma_age %in% miss_values_vector)]

# Update of global table
assign_merge <- function(endtib, sttib, log_vec = c(T), col_end_index = NULL, 
    col_st_index = NULL) {
    newtib <- full_join(endtib, sttib, by = "id")
    row.names(newtib) <- newtib$id
    newtib[log_vec, col_end_index] <- newtib[log_vec, col_st_index]
    id_ind <- match("id", names(newtib))
    newtib <- newtib[, c(id_ind, col_end_index)]
    names(newtib)[2] <- "x"
    newtib$x <- car::recode(newtib$x, "NA=999")
    names(newtib)[2] <- names(endtib)[col_end_index]
    newtib
}
ELSA_ds_prov <- ELSA_ds[, c(1, 2)]
ELSA_ds_prov <- assign_merge(ELSA_ds_prov, ELSA_ds_w4, log_vec = ELSA_ds_w4$id, 
    col_end_index = 2, col_st_index = 3)
ELSA_ds_aux <- ELSA_ds[, c(1, 3)]
ELSA_ds_aux <- assign_merge(ELSA_ds_aux, ELSA_ds_w4, log_vec = ELSA_ds_w4$id[which(ELSA_ds_w4$h_asthma != 
    999)], col_end_index = 2, col_st_index = 4)
ELSA_ds <- ELSA_ds_prov
ELSA_ds$h_asthma_age <- ELSA_ds_aux$h_asthma_age
rm(ELSA_ds_prov)
rm(ELSA_ds_aux)
